I"Å<p>Working with kvm/qemu involves using libguestfs-tools sometimes in order to prep the deployment of servers. Iâ€™ve come across the issue of read/writing to FreeBSD partitions using the mount tool. Even though itâ€™s 2015, the Linux Kernel still has experimental write support for UFS. Hereâ€™s how to recompile your kernel with ufs write support.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>apt-get <span class="nb">install </span>linux-source kernel-package
